{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2018}} {{Infobox sportsperson | name = Eduard Antoch | image = | alt = | caption = | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = <!-- {{death-date and age|23 August 1981|1 October 1949}} --> | death_place = | residence = | education = | alma_mater = | occupation = | years_active = | spouse = | sport = Rowing | club = | medaltemplates = {{MedalSport|Men's [[Rowing (sport)|rowing]]}} {{MedalCountry|{{TCH}}}} {{MedalCompetition | [[European Rowing Championships]] }} {{MedalGold | [[1956 European Rowing Championships|1956 Bled]] | Eight}} }} '''Eduard Antoch''' is a Czechoslovak [[Rowing (sport)|rower]]. He competed at the [[1956 European Rowing Championships]] in [[Bled]], Yugoslavia, with the men's eight where they won the gold medal.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Heckert |first1=Karlheinz |title=Rudern – Europameisterschaften (Herren – Achter) |url= http://www.sport-komplett.de/sport-komplett/sportarten/r/rudern/hst/69.html |publisher=Sport Komplett |accessdate=8 March 2018| language=de}}</ref> The same team went to the [[1956 Summer Olympics]] in [[Melbourne]] with the [[Rowing at the 1956 Summer Olympics – Men's eight|men's eight]] where they were eliminated in the semi-final.<ref name="FISA profile">{{cite web |title= Eduard Antoch |url= http://www.worldrowing.com/athletes/athlete/28841/results/ |publisher=[[International Rowing Federation]] |accessdate=8 March 2018}}</ref><ref name="SR profile">{{Cite sports-reference | Eduard Antoch | https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/an/eduard-antoch-1.html | 8 March 2018 }}</ref>
