{{For|the fictional character|Houngan (Clayfighter)}}
{{Refimprove|date=December 2009}}

'''''Houngan''''' is the term for a male [[priest]] in [[Haitian Vodou]] (a female priest is known as a ''[[Mambo (Vodou)|mambo]]'').<ref>{{cite web|last=Corbett|first=Bob|title=INTRODUCTION TO VOODOO IN HAITI|url=http://www.webster.edu/~corbetre/haiti/voodoo/overview.htm|accessdate=14 October 2011|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111006144910/http://www.webster.edu/~corbetre/haiti/voodoo/overview.htm|archivedate=6 October 2011|df=}}</ref> The term is derived from the [[Fon language|Fon]] word "''[[hùn gan|Hounnongan]]''. There are two ranks of ''houngan'': '''''houngan asogwe''''' (high priest) and '''''houngan sur pwen''''' (junior priest).<ref>{{cite web|title=WORD MEANINGS AND REFERENCES|url=http://theoriginalpapabones.com/blog/?page_id=1004|work=THE AMERICAN VOODOO SOCIETY & THE GEDE NATIONS|accessdate=14 October 2011}}{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> A ''houngan asogwe'' is the highest member of clergy in voodoo and the only one with authority to ordain other priests.

It is the ''houngan'''s role to preserve the rituals and songs and maintain the relationship between the spirits and the community as a whole (though some of this is the responsibility of the whole community as well). They are entrusted with leading the service of all of the spirits of their lineage. Sometimes they may also be ''[[bokor]]'' (sorcerers).

