i]] (1894–1964){{spaced ndash}} founder, [[Gozo Party]]; member, [[Parliament of Malta]] (1947–1950) * Sir [[Ugo Pasquale Mifsud]] (1889–1942){{spaced ndash}} [[Prime Minister of Malta]] (1932–1933) * [[Karmenu Mifsud Bonnici]] (born 1933){{spaced ndash}} [[Prime Minister of Malta]] (1984–1987) * [[Ugo Mifsud Bonnici]] (born 1932){{spaced ndash}} [[minister (government)|government minister]]; [[President of Malta]] (1994–1999) * [[Dom Mintoff]] (1916–2012){{spaced ndash}} [[Prime Minister of Malta]] (1955–1958, 1971–1984) * [[Enrico Mizzi]] (1885–1950){{spaced ndash}} [[Prime Minister of Malta]] (1950) * [[Joseph Muscat]] (born 1974){{spaced ndash}} [[Member of the European Parliament]] (2004–2008); leader, [[Labour Party (Malta)|Labour Party]] (since 2008), [[Prime Minister of Malta]] (since 2013) * [[Guglielmo Rapinett]] (1843–1912){{spaced ndash}} member, Council of Government * [[Alfred Sant]] (born 1948){{spaced ndash}} [[Prime Minister of Malta]] (1996–1998) * [[Gerald Strickland]] (1861–1940){{spaced ndash}} [[Prime Minister of Malta]] (1927–1932); [[Governor of Tasmania]]; [[Governor of Western Australia]]; [[Governor of New South Wales]] * [[Ċensu Tabone]] (1913–2012){{spaced ndash}} [[minister (government)|government minister]]; [[President of Malta]] (1989–1994) * [[George William Vella]] (born 1942){{spaced ndash}} [[minister (government)|government minister]]; [[Deputy Prime Minister of Malta]] (1996–1998) * [[Paul Xuereb]] (1923–1994){{spaced ndash}} [[Speaker of the House of Representatives of Malta]] (1986–1987); Acting [[President of Malta]] (1987–1989) {{div col end}}
